'''Deiver Andrés Machado Mena''' (born 2 September 1993) is a Colombian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left-back]] or [[left wing-back]] for [[Ligue 1]] club [[FC Nantes|Nantes]] and the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia national team]].

== Club career ==
In 2020, Deiver Machado joined [[Ligue 2]] club [[Toulouse FC|Toulouse]] as a free agent.

On 2 July 2021, he joined [[Ligue 1]] club [[RC Lens|Lens]] for three years.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Transferts : Deiver Machado (Toulouse) signe à RC Lens |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Transferts-deiver-machado-toulouse-signe-a-rc-lens/1268776 |access-date=2023-01-31 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref> On 31 January, he extended his contract with Lens until 2026.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-01-31 |title=Mercato : Deiver Machado prolonge dans la durée à Lens |url=https://www.lefigaro.fr/sports/football/transferts/mercato-deiver-machado-prolonge-dans-la-duree-a-lens-20230131 |access-date=2023-01-31 |website=LEFIGARO |language=fr}}</ref>

On 8 December 2025, Machado joined Ligue 1 club [[FC Nantes|Nantes]] on a transfer, signing a three-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-12-08 |title=Deiver Machado rejoint le FC Nantes ! |url=https://www.fcnantes.com/articles/article2809.php?num=48247 |publisher=FC Nantes |language=fr}}</ref>

==International career==
Machado was named in the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia national team]]'s provisional squad for [[Copa América Centenario]] but was cut from the final squad.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goal.com/en-us/news/587/copa-america/2016/05/04/23144402/falcao-left-out-of-colombias-copa-america-squad|title=Falcao left out of Colombia's Copa America squad|publisher=goal.com |date=4 May 2016 |accessdate=11 July 2016}}</ref>

